description:
'''Nelson Cândido Motta Filho''' (born 29 October 1944, [[São Paulo|São Paulo, Brazil]]) is a Brazilian [[journalist]], [[ghostwriter]], [[songwriter]], writer, and [[record producer]].

He was part of the [[bossa nova]] movement, collaborating with [[Edu Lobo]], [[Dori Caymmi]], [[Lulu Santos]], [[Rita Lee]], [[Djavan]] and others, and producer for several [[Música popular brasileira|MPB]] artists, such as [[Elis Regina]], [[Gal Costa]], [[Daniela Mercury]] and others. He was [[Marisa Monte]]'s first music producer in the late 1980s. Motta also produced early [[Brazilian rock]] shows and wrote lyrics in collaboration with rock artists, such as [[Lulu Santos]].{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}

He produced ''Riû'', the third album of the Portuguese [[fado]] singer [[Cuca Roseta]], released in 2015.
